"{\"uid\": \"thefederalist.com-2024-07-29-olympic-drag-themed-parody-of-last-supper-scene-will-drag-down-gay-acceptance\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Mocking one's religious neighbors with an outright blasphemous display of fetishism to validate fringe sexual desires is anything but normal.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics is an opportunity for host nations to celebrate their cultural contributions to the world.\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Apparently, the French are most proud of mocking Christians under the shadow of Notre Dame.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 263, \"end\": 269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9946144911566589, \"rank\": 0.00541163902312423, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 296, \"end\": 306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.987266260783746, \"rank\": 0.01270114404467369, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not straight and I am not baptized, but you do not have to be either to be repelled by the openly naked ugliness on display at the Paris Olympics Friday night.\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What was France trying to say of itself with a drag-themed parody to mock one of the holiest scenes in Christianity?\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 515, \"end\": 521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.6588090283646096, \"rank\": 0.5016050842295678, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999783621614344, \"rank\": 2.1637108976772227e-05, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Was this an image of France as an oasis of global inclusion?\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 644, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.6588090283646096, \"rank\": 0.5016050842295678, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or was it a neopaganistic expression of 21st-century transformation against the background of the world-famous 14th-century cathedral?\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Recentelectionslargely reflected a French population frustrated by mass migration, and they certainlystill do not love\\\"body positivity,\\\" so it is probably more so the latter.\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9946144911566589, \"rank\": 0.00541163902312423, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French also have a recent history ofpersecutingChristians, so do not expect those who were mocked on Friday night to be all that included when these people take over.\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 999, \"end\": 1005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9946144911566589, \"rank\": 0.00541163902312423, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And let us not pretend the performance, whichfeatured a child, was an exercise in honoring the biblical supper scene because everybody knows Christians see drag as a manifestation of some underlying evil.\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1307, \"end\": 1317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.987266260783746, \"rank\": 0.01270114404467369, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gay movement took decades to convince its Christian neighbors that gays were normal.\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1418, \"end\": 1427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9991236857194755, \"rank\": 0.0008770828808295694, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, mocking one's religious neighbors with an outright blasphemous display of fetishism to validate fringe sexual desires is anything but normal.\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's one thing to put a drag queen on a platform, and it's another to weaponize an art perceived by Christians as demonic to demand their approval.\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.987266260783746, \"rank\": 0.01270114404467369, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What activists often forget is that, much like politics, culture is a pendulum, and how far it swings in one direction will determine how far it swings in the other.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Republicans onlyremovedan explicit endorsement for heterosexual marriage this year, but those changes are not permanent, and recent polling suggests the beginning of a recoil.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 2102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1927, \"end\": 1938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"score\": 0.9999921375328861, \"rank\": 7.842560529351181e-06, \"text\": \"Republicans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republicanism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The backlash against transgenderism already started.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last year,several surveysrevealed steep declines in support for transgenderism, specifically related to biological men competing in women's sports.\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sliding approval numbers in support for homosexuality have just begun after the trans movement attached itself to the gay movement in an effort to gain public acceptance.\", \"from\": 2305, \"to\": 2479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2389, \"end\": 2394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"score\": 0.9999997587761136, \"rank\": 2.2752854890547714e-07, \"text\": \"trans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New data from the Public Religion Research Institute (PRRI)showedin March that support for gay marriage fell between 2022 and 2023 for the first time in nearly a decade.\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2498, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public_Religion_Research_Institute\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Public Religion Research Institute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public_Religion_Research_Institute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Public_Religion_Research_Institute\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RecentGallupsurveys have corroborated the findings of support for same-sex marriage in decline, with 69 percent of Americans favoring \\\"marriages between homosexuals\\\" in May compared to 71 percent who said the same in 2022 and 2023.\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sexuality is not very interesting, and homosexuality became accepted and normalized when it stopped being interesting.\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 3001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gay people stopped shocking us on films and television shows such as \\\"Will & Grace\\\" because most of our neighbors came to know a gay person, or a few.\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Does that mean we should start putting transvestite drag performers on family broadcasts to mock the Christians?\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3254, \"end\": 3264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.987266260783746, \"rank\": 0.01270114404467369, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's not normal behavior, so no one else wants to normalize that.\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3333, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jillian Michaels is a lesbian mom who recently fled California in part over the state'scascadeof legislation promoting child gender transitions even without parental notice.\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3335, \"end\": 3351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jillian_Michaels\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jillian Michaels\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jillian_Michaels\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jillian_Michaels\"}, {\"begin\": 3387, \"end\": 3397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 0.999999957584806, \"rank\": 3.93995814966452e-08, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I grew up here.\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am a woman.\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am a gay woman.\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My mom's a Jew.\", \"from\": 3559, \"to\": 3574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3570, \"end\": 3573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 0.785834373284316, \"rank\": 0.27253277906926554, \"text\": \"Jew\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My dad's an Arab.\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3587, \"end\": 3591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"score\": 0.8172225017337483, \"rank\": 0.20123963365893688, \"text\": \"Arab\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arab_world\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have a black kid.\", \"from\": 3593, \"to\": 3612, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And believe it or not, my son is half Latin, even though he does not look like it,\\\" Michaelsexplainedon a recent podcast.\", \"from\": 3613, \"to\": 3734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hold a million cards in your game of woke victimology poker.\", \"from\": 3735, \"to\": 3798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And when I leave California, maybe you have lost your f-ing mind.\\\"\", \"from\": 3799, \"to\":